<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="1360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1360">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–2645: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1360<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United
                                    Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26T17:00:00+01:00">July 26, 1945—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7529. FonOff now states French Govt will be informed immediately
                                British concurrence in Soviet participation Tangier discussions and
                                that French and British Govts will communicate with Moscow upon
                                concerting their action. (Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                                as 7529; repeated Paris as 484; repeated Tangier as 47; repeated
                                Madrid as 200).</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_WJG2"><hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>